  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Support to flood affected communities in Bihar (Katihar) and Uttar Pradesh (Bahraich)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1800 HHs access to essential hygiene materials leading to improved health outcomes through treatment of water and safe confinement of solid and liquid waste in the surroundings.
8000 people in targeted places will have access to safe drinking water through community water filters to be safe from water born diseases
1800 HHs and others in the community will have improved protection against the floods and ongoing monsoons with the capacity to demonstrate improvement in hygiene conditions and behaviour. 
1800 most vulnerable HHs will get household NFIs to meet their basic needs. 
1800 most vulnerable HHs have received shelter NFIs including tarpaulin and ground sheeting to ensure provision of emergency shelter. 
20000 people are aware of the good hygiene practices to protect themselves from diseases with hygiene promotion</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A. Hygiene kits given to 1800 households, family size = 5 members, overall beneficiaries = 9000 people
B. Community water filters  8 numbers will cover 1000 people per days,  overall beneficiaries = 8000 people 
C. Emergency shelter support provided to 1800 households = 5 members overall beneficiaries = 9000 people                                      
D. NFI support provided to 1800 households, family size = 5 members, overall beneficiaries = 9000 people
E. Hygiene promotion campaign carried out in target villages with a total of around 20,000 people</narrative>
  </description>
